s/|title=Real Estates at Peer Gallery}}</ref>\n*''Common Ground'' (solo), Spike Island, Bristol (2017)<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.spikeisland.org.uk/programme/exhibitions/andrea-luka-zimmerman/|title=Andrea Luka Zimmerman, Common Ground at Spike Island, Bristol|website=Spike Island|language=en|access-date=2019-02-24}}</ref>\n*London Open (group), triennial at [[Whitechapel Gallery]] (2018)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0b5qnjs|title=Exam stress, Artist Andrea Luka Zimmerman, 50-50 music festivals, Woman's Hour - BBC Radio 4|website=BBC|access-date=2018-07-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thisistomorrow.info/articles/andrea-luka-zimmerman-civil-rites|title=Andrea Luka Zimmerman: Civil Rites|last=www.dandelion-burdock.com|first=dandelion & burdock|website=thisistomorrow|access-date=2018-07-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://narcmagazine.com/news-andrea-luka-zimmermans-civil-rites-tyneside-gallery/|title=NEWS: Andrea Luka Zimmerman's Civil Rites @ Tyneside Gallery|access-date=2018-07-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mapmagazine.co.uk/civil-rites|title=Civil Rites|date=2018-02-01|work=MAP Magazine|access-date=2018-07-15}}</ref>\n\n== Books ==\n*Co-author of ''Estate: Art, Politics and Social Housing in Britain'': Myrdle Court Press,''<nowiki/>'' 2010 {{ISBN|978-0-9563539-2-4}}\n*Contribution in ''Truth, Dare or Promise: Art and Document<nowiki/>ary Revisited''. London & New York: Cambridge Scholars Publishing, 2013, {{ISBN| 9781443849593}}. (Edited by Gail Pearce, Jill Daniels, Cahal McLaughlin)\n*Featured in ''With Dogs At The End of Life'': Columbia University Press, 2015, Colin Dayan {{ISBN| 9780231167123}}.\n*Featured in ''Political Animals: The New Feminist Cinema'': I.B. Tauris, 2016, So Mayer {{ISBN| 0857729942}}.\n*Featured in [https://books.google.co.uk/books?hl=en&lr=&id=Z0eTDAAAQBAJ&oi=fnd&pg=PA103&dq=andrea+luka+zimmerman&ots=UIS0e2U8Ql&sig=rcFs7HMPDMhvraNiFwd8_QpNj_k#v=onepage&q=andrea%20luka%20zimmerman&f=false ''The Routledge Companion to Cinema and Politics'']: edited by Yannis Tzioumakis, Claire Molloy, 2016 {{ISBN| 978-0415717397}}.\n*Featured in [https://www.bloomsbury.com/uk/non-cinema-9781501327292/ ''Non-Cinema: Global Digital Film-making and the Multitude''], William Brown, 2018,{{ISBN| 9781501327292}}.''<nowiki/><nowiki/>''\n*Featured in ''[https://riviste.unimi.it/index.php/AMonline/article/view/10833 Other Modernities]'' in conversation with Caterina Sartori, Universit\u00e0 degli Studi d''<nowiki/><nowiki/>''i Milano, 2018,\u00a0ISSN 2035-7680 \n*Contribution and co-editor of ''Doorways: Women, Homelessness, Trauma and Resistance, '<nowiki/>''Persona (Non) Grata: Reading the Human in the \u2018Homeless\u2019 as part of ''<nowiki/>'''Two Reflections on Art and Neoliberalism' - Shiri Shalmy and Andrea Luka Zimmerman on cultural production under capitalism and the role of art and artists in a social crisis, House Sparrow Press, 2019<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.housesparrowpress.com/|title=Home|website=House Sparrow Press|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref> \n*Contribution in Annual Art Journal ISSUE 08, ERASE, ''[http://ualresearchonline.arts.ac.uk/14735/ On Erasure],'' Lasalle College of th''<nowiki/>''e Arts, 2019, ISSN 2315-4802\n*Contribution in ''[https://www.anothergaze.com/category/news/ Another Gaze,]'' a Feminist Film Journal, Vol 04, ''Otherwise: Notes on Be<nowiki/>ing Perennially In-Between,'' [https://ualresearchonline.arts.ac.uk/id/eprint/15580/6/AG04_AZ%26TH.pdf pp. 30-35], 2020 ISBN 25163876\n\n== Articles ==\n*[https://www.studiointernational.com/index.php/andrea-luka-zimmerman-interview-here-for-life-film Andrea Luka Zimmerman Interview] ''<nowiki/>''[https://www.studiointernational.com/index.php/andrea-luka-zimmerman-interview-here-for-life-film - Here For Life], Studio International, 2019\n\n*Secreting History - Screening \u2018History\u2019: 21 takes in \"La Furia Umana\"  LFU/36],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lafuriaumana.it/index.php/69-lfu-36/888-andrea-luka-zimmerman-secreting-history-screening-history-21-takes|title=ANDREA LUKA ZIMMERMAN / Secreting History - Screening 'History': 21 takes|website=www.lafuriaumana.it|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref> April 2019\n*Text for the Living School publication, conceived and ed. by Brandon LaBelle (for South London Gallery), 2018. [http://www.brandonlabelle.net/texts/Liviing_School.pdf]\n\n*Co-existence: A modest proposal for preventing the street dogs of Istanbul from being a burden on their neighbourhoods and citizenry, in SEQUENCE New Artists' Film and Video, Vol 4., ed. Simon Payne, no.w.here, 2016, pp.36-38\n\n*[https://www.focaalblog.com/2015/04/23/andrea-luka-zimmerman-estates-of-being/ Estates of Being: Thoughts on the place of living and working], Focaalblog, 2015\n\n*Human Conditions: the Lives of Estate/s in \"La Furia Umana\", [http://www.lafuriaumana.it/index.php/56-lfu-23/328-andrea-luka-zimmermann-human-conditions-the-lives-of-estate-s] April 2015\n\n*Amsler; Pinder; Hope; Owen; Roberts; Shah; Zimmerman; Theron Schmidt; a response to Beyond Glorious, the Radical in Engaged Practices, Rajni Shah; in \u2018CTR Backpages 24.2\u2019, Contemporary Theatre Review, Routledge, Vol. 24, No. 2, 284\u2013299, May 2014\n\n*The Certainty of Uncertainty (Zimmerman / Roberts), in \u201cLondon\u2019s Regeneration Realities\u201d, ed. Ben Campkin, David Roberts, Rebecca Ross. Urban Lab, 12/2013\n\n*Truth, Dare or Promise: Art and Documentary Revisited. (text and image): Homeland (In)Securities, ed Jill Daniels, Cahal McLaughlin and Gail Pearce, Camebridge Press, 11/2013\n\n*[https://www.opendemocracy.net/andrea-luka-zimmerman/on-common-ground-making-of-meaning-in-film-and-life On common ground: the making of meaning in film and life], Open Democracy, 2013\n*Estate in three Parts. Text, Image and moving image for The Home and The World, Dartington, online publication, 10/2013\n\n*Thinking in Practice, Balmond Studio. Re-imagining Council Housi